#1 Rectosigmoid cancer and synchronous adenoma at the hepatic flexure
Mrs. Sternberg presents for further evaluation and treatment of colorectal cancer.  I discussed the development, staging, and treatment of colorectal cancer with her as well as Lynch syndrome given the development of these growths in her bowel at such a young age.  We will proceed with lab work, chest x-ray, ECG, and CT abdomen and pelvis for staging purposes, as well as EUS and colonoscopy to assess for nodal involvement and confirm the location as sigmoid and not rectal.  Patient will then meet with Colon and Rectal Surgery for surgical recommendations.  She is also agreeable to immunohistochemistry staining to assess for Lynch syndrome.  Brochures given.
#2 Preoperative medical evaluation
Lab work, chest x-ray, and ECG (given her history of occasional heart palpitation) are pending.  Once these are obtained and satisfactory, the patient is OK for anesthesia.
Discussed with Dr. Kerry Snow, note to follow.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

[end section id="20112"]

[start section id="20102"]

